    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Diagnostics Manual - Electronic Control Systems Diagnostics - Circuit Diagnostics - IAH (Inlet
        Air Heater) Circuit
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s305010706.23" svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="5">
        <title>IAH (Inlet Air Heater) Circuit</title>
        <svcprocinfo id="s305010706.23.1">
            <figure id="f3050107107" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/j31146.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="592px"/>
                <caption>Function diagram for Inlet Air Heater</caption>
            </figure>
            <para id="s305010706.21.1.1"></para>
            <table id="t3050107222" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>The function diagram for the IAH system includes the following:</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Inlet Air Heater (IAH)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Inlet Air Heater relay</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Electronic Control Module (ECM)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Engine Oil Temperature (EOT) sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Barometric Absolute Pressure (BAP) sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Mass Air Flow/Inlet Air Heater (MAF/IAT) sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>WAIT TO START lamp</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Battery</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <title>Function</title>The inlet air heater control system warms the air entering the intake manifold to
                aid cold engine starting and reduce exhaust emissions during warm-up.
            </para>
            <para>The ECM is programmed to energize the inlet air heater (through the inlet air heater relay) while
                monitoring programmed conditions for engine oil temperature, inlet air temperature, and atmospheric
                pressure.
            </para>
            <para>The ECM monitors battery voltage and uses information from the Barometric Absolute Pressure (BAP)
                sensor, the Inlet Air Temperature (IAT), and the Engine Oil Temperature (EOT) sensor to determine the
                amount of time that the WAIT TO START lamp is ON and the activation time of the inlet air heater. The
                ECM controls the WAIT TO START lamp and the activation of the inlet air heater separately.
            </para>
            <para>Inlet air heater is activated if the engine is cold or the barometric pressure is low (high
                altitude).
            </para>
            <para>The engine is ready to start when the WAIT TO START lamp is turned off by the ECM.</para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="s305010706.23.2">
            <title>IAH Circuit Operation</title>
            <figure id="f3050107108" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/j31203.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="532px"/>
                <caption>IAH circuit diagram</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The inlet air heater control system operation on time depends on IAT, EOT, BAP, and battery voltage.
                The inlet air heater relay is activated by power supplied by the ECM through Pin X1-18 to the IAHC
                circuit. The coil of the inlet air heater relay is grounded through the actuator power ground circuit,
                Pin 4 of the 12-pin connector to the battery negative terminal. Power is supplied to the switch side of
                the inlet air heater relay from the starter motor. When the relay coil is energized, power is supplied
                to the inlet air heater that is grounded through the intake manifold.
            </para>
            <para>The ECM monitors the output of the relay, from the relay to Pin X2-11.</para>
            <para>The WAIT TO START lamp time is transmitted over the CAN1 datalink. See the applicable truck Circuit
                Diagram Manual.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>Fault Detection/Management</title>The ECM continuously monitors the output of the IAH relay, when
                voltage is not as expected a DTC will be set.
            </para>
            <para>An open or short to ground in the inlet air heater relay control circuit can be detected by an on
                demand Output Circuit Check (OCC) performed during the KOEO Standard test. When a circuit fault is
                detected, a DTC will be set. Inlet air heater and inlet air heater wiring problems can not be detected
                by the ECM.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>IAH DTCs</title>DTCs are read using the EST or by counting the flashes from the amber and red
                lamps.
            </para>
            <table id="t3050107223" tblwidth="col-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>DTC 238</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Inlet Air Heater Control OCC self-test failed</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>DTC 238 is set by the ECM when the OCC test has failed after the KOEO Standard
                                    test has been run.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>DTC 238 can be set for an open or shorted IAHC circuit, an open actuator power
                                    ground, or an open IAH relay coil.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <table id="t3050107224" tblwidth="col-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>DTC 373</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Inlet Air Heater relay circuit fault</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>DTC 373 is set by the ECM when the relay output voltage does not meet the expected
                                    voltage.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>DTC 373 can be set for an open in the B+ supply circuit to the IAH relay, open or
                                    shorted IAHD circuit, or a failed IAH relay.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>DTC 373 can be set if there is a failed control circuit, repair DTC 238 first.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
